### CSS Links

Style `<a>` elements in different states.

---

### Link States (Pseudo-Classes)

| State | Pseudo-Class | Description |
|-------|-------------|-------------|
| `:link` | Default | Unvisited link |
| `:visited` | Visited | Already clicked |
| `:hover` | Hover | Mouse over link |
| `:active` | Active | Being clicked |

**Order matters - LVHA:** `:link`, `:visited`, `:hover`, `:active`

---

### Basic Link Styling

```css
a {
  color: #3498db;
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: color 0.2s;
}

a:visited {
  color: #8e44ad;
}

a:hover {
  color: #2980b9;
  text-decoration: underline;
}

a:active {
  color: #1a5276;
}
```

---

### Link Underline Styles

```css
a {
  text-decoration: none;
  position: relative;
}

a::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: currentColor;
  transition: width 0.3s;
}

a:hover::after {
  width: 100%;
}
```

---

### Link Button Style

```css
a.button {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 12px 24px;
  background: #3498db;
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-radius: 6px;
  transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
}

a.button:hover {
  background: #2980b9;
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}
```

---

### External Link Indicator

```css
a[target="_blank"]::after {
  content: " \u2197";
  font-size: 0.8em;
}

a[href^="http"]:not([href*="mysite.com"])::after {
  content: " \u2197";
}
```

---

### Accessibility

```css
a:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #3498db;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

---

> **Best Practice:** Follow LVHA order. Always remove default underline with `text-decoration: none` and add custom hover styles.
